[MK] case called at 4:13am.
Defendant Clifton N Parker in court with Attorney Whitney Hagemann.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court sentences Mr. Parker to serve 9 months in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; consecutive to any other sentence. Mr. Parker is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in his system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
Days credit for time already served:  5 days. The Court allows the State one week to file any challenge to this amount of days credit by either pursuing a stipulation or requesting a hearing.  

The Court STAYS this sentences and places Mr. Parker on Probation for one year with conditions:
--no possession or consumption of illegal drugs
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling as required by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand 
-to pay a fine of $250 plus costs, fees, assessments, and surcharges including the DNA surcharge 

The Court requires Mr. Parker to report to the Probation Office in Jefferson by end of business tomorrow. 
Felony firearm prohibition warnings are given
recess 4:30pm.
